Executive Profile
John L. Ocampo  Co-founder and President, Gaas Labs, LLCAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 2 Board Members in 2 different organizations across 5 different industries.See Board Relationships58--
Background

		Mr. John L. Ocampo co-founded Gaas Labs, LLC and has been its President since November 2007. Mr. Ocampo served as Chief Technology Officer of Sirenza Microdevices Inc., from May 1999 to September 2002 and President and Chief Executive Officer from 1984 to May 1999. From 1982 to 1984, He served as a General Manager at Magnum Microwave. From 1980 to 1982, he served as Engineering Manager at Avantek. He has been the Chairman of the Board of MACOM Technology Solutions Holdings, ... Inc. since March 2009. He serves as the Chairman of MACOM Technology Solutions Inc. since March 2009. He Co-founded Sirenza Microdevices Inc. and served as its Chairman from December 1998 to November 2007. Mr. Ocampo served as the Chairman of Mimix Broadband, Inc. He has been a Member of Advisory Board at RFaxis, Inc., since June 2011. He serves on the Board of Trustees of Santa Clara University. He served as a Director of Ubiquiti Networks, Inc., from October 2010 to October 25, 2013; Sirenza Microdevices Inc., from 1985 to November 2007 and Qorvo, Inc. from December 3, 2007 to May 21, 2008. Mr. Ocampo holds a B.S.E.E. degree from the Santa Clara University.Read Full Background




