Insider Activity


Individual




John L. Ocampo



Mr. John L. Ocampo is Co-Founder & President at Gaas Labs, Inc. Prior to his affiliation with GaAs Labs, Mr. Ocampo co-foundered Sirenza Microdevices, Inc. and served as the company's Chairman. He was a Director of RF Micro Devices, Inc. until May 19, 2008.  He also served as Chief Technology Officer of Sirenza from May 1999 to September 2002, and as President and Chief Executive Officer from 1984 to May 1999. From 1982 to 1984, he served as General Manager at Magnum Microwave. And from 1980 to 1982, he served as Engineering Manager at Avantek, a telecommunications engineering company, now Hewlett-Packard/Avantek.
Mr. Ocampo received a BSEE from Santa Clara University.



