John Chambers, 51President, CEOCisco, San Jose, CA17.0M/$426.4M   NET Cisco had a market cap of $600 million and annual sales of $1.2 billion when Chambers took the helm in January 1995. He has been, shall we say, successful: Last spring Cisco's market cap exceeded $500 billion and annual sales hit 12.2 billion. The stock subsequently tumbled with the rest of the tech industry, shaving $770 million off Chambers' fortune by year's end. But don't feel too bad�at least he has friends to lean on. Last June, Indiana University endowed a $1.2 million chair in his name at its Kelley School of Business.


